THE COVID-19 pandemic played havoc with the United Nations’ Sustainable Development Goals. Progress to achieve gender equality by 2030 has not only stalled, it’s reversed. Host Anne McElvoy asks Melinda French Gates, a philanthropist, if the target still makes sense. The co-chair of the Gates Foundation also discusses the overturning of Roe v Wade in America. Run time: 21 min  Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn